 Business Briefs
																								 New Delhi, Oct. 22: Warring Bajaj brothers Rahul and Shishir today resumed their legal battle in the Company Law Board (CLB) over division of the business empire after failing to reach an out-of-court settlement. During proceedings before the principle bench of the CLB, Rahuls counsel Ashok Desai said the group patriarch last week made an offer to his younger sibling, who turned it down.																								 New Delhi, Oct. 22: The Aditya Birla group will increase its cement production capacity by almost 50 per cent to 46 million tonnes in a year, as it seeks to increase its sales and gain a higher market share. 																								 New Delhi, Oct. 22: Pakistan has invited India for talks next month to resolve the transit fee issue over which New Delhi had boycotted last months trilateral discussions in Tehran on the Iran-Pakistan-India gas pipeline.																								 New Delhi, Oct. 22: ONGC-Mittal Energy (Omel), a joint venture of ONGC Videsh and Mittal Investment, has acquired a 30 per cent stake in an exploration block in offshore Turkmenistan in the Caspian sea.																								 New Delhi, Oct. 22: Family-owned companies are dominating the Indian corporate landscape, but still face challenges regarding corporate governance norms, rating agency Moodys said.
